Here's an example of how to create a simple PDF template with a text field using Adobe Acrobat Pro:

Open Adobe Acrobat Pro and create a new PDF document.

Go to the "Prepare Form" tool in the right-hand pane.
Click "Start" and select the "Text Field" tool.
Drag the text field onto the PDF document where you want it to appear.
Right-click on the text field and select "Properties."
Give the text field a unique name or field ID, such as "patientName".
Save the PDF document.
